<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <%- include('../partials/head'); %>
    <title>GM Build Counts</title>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('../partials/header'); %>
    <div class="custom-container">
        <div class="content">
            <div class="container-fluid">
                <h2 class="pt-4">Introduction</h2>
                <p>Visit the Vehicles page from the header and click on a vehicle row to access further information of that vehicle.</p>
                <img src="../img/index/vehicleTable.png" class="img-fluid mb-3" alt="Vehicle Table">
                <p class="pt-3">Allow some time (<1 minute) for the photos to generate</p>
                <img src="../img/index/individualVehicle.png" class="img-fluid mb-3" alt="Individual Vehicle">
                <p class="pt-3">
                    Below the photos will be the Window Sticker if available - North American vehicles only<br>
                    GM 'hides' JSON data at the very top of each sticker which includes all of the data used to supply information throughout this site.<br>
                    You can see this by clicking inside the window sticker document and pressing the keys CTRL+A (Select All), CTRL+C (Copy) and open a notepad to paste CTRL+V (Paste).<br>
                    The JSON is at the very bottom of the document when pasted following these steps.
                </p>
                <img src="../img/index/window-sticker-info.png" class="img-fluid mb-3" alt="Window Sticker">
                <p class="pt-3">Click the See Rarity button to calculate the number of cars built with the exact same RPO codes</p>
                <img src="../img/index/rarity.png" class="img-fluid mb-3" alt="Rarity Button">
                <p class="pt-3">The bottom table lists all associated RPO codes and their descriptions</p>
                <img src="../img/index/rpo-info.png" class="img-fluid mb-3" alt="RPO Info">
            </div>
        </div>
    <%- include('../partials/footer'); %>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
